NAME
       less - paginated file viewer with regex search

SYNOPSIS
       less [-N] [FILE]

DESCRIPTION
       Reads FILE (or stdin) into memory and displays it one screenful
       at a time. Search uses the libcervus regex(3) engine with POSIX
       extended syntax. The status line shows the filename, current
       line range, and percentage through the document.

OPTIONS
       -N    show line numbers in the left margin

KEYS
       q, Ctrl-C       quit
       h               help screen
       j, down         scroll one line down
       k, up           scroll one line up
       space, PgDn     scroll one page down
       b, PgUp         scroll one page up
       g, Home         jump to first line
       G, End          jump to last line
       /PATTERN        search forward
       ?PATTERN        search backward
       n               repeat last search in same direction
       N               repeat last search in opposite direction
       =, F            toggle line numbers
       Esc             cancel an in-progress prompt

SEARCH
       PATTERN is compiled as a POSIX extended regular expression.
       Matches are highlighted on every visible line. The status line
       reports "pattern not found" when a search fails.

EXAMPLES
       less /etc/motd
       cat big.log | less
       less -N /apps/shell.c

SEE ALSO
       man(1), grep(1), regex(3)
